sentences: Tina Pinnock, (born July 4, 1991) known professionally as HoodCelebrityy, is a Jamaican dancehall singer and songwriter.
Currently signed to Epic Records, she released two mixtapes in 2017, Can't Believe It's Just a Girl and Trap Vs.
Her 2017 single, "Walking Trophy," peaked at number 22 on the R&B/Hip-Hop Airplay chart.
HoodCelebrityy's breakout came in 2015 when friend and future collaborator, Cardi B, posted about her song, "Wine Pon It".
In 2016, HoodCelebrityy was featured on the Jubilee song, "Wine Up."
In January 2017, she appeared on Cardi B's mixtape, Gangsta Bitch Music, Vol. 2, on the song "Back It Up" which also featured Konshens.
In August 2017, HoodCelebrityy released her second mixtape, Trap Vs.
Later in 2017, she released the single, "Walking Trophy."
The video for "Walking Trophy" was directed by Mazi O and released in February 2018.
In May 2018, HoodCelebrityy was signed to Epic Records.
On August 30, 2019 HoodCelebrityy released a single called "Bum Pon It" on her Official Youtube page.
She performed at the 2018 Summer Jam.
Currently signed to Epic Records, she released two mixtapes in 2017, Can't Believe It's Just a Girl and Trap Vs.
That same month, she released the lead single, "The Takeover", off of her debut mixtape, Can't Believe It's Just a Girl.
The mixtape was released in the spring of that year.
Later that month, she and Tory Lanez were featured on the Megan Ryte track, "On & On."
